---
import ArticleFooter from "@/components/article/ArticleFooter.astro";
import ArticleHeader from "@/components/article/ArticleHeader.astro";
import ArticleHero from "@/components/article/ArticleHero.astro";
import ArticleSection from "@/components/article/ArticleSection.astro";
import ArticleShell from "@/components/article/ArticleShell.astro";
import BackgroundMeta from "@/components/article/BackgroundMeta.astro";
import FeatureList from "@/components/article/FeatureList.astro";
import InsightList from "@/components/article/InsightList.astro";
import MediaFigure from "@/components/article/MediaFigure.astro";
import NumberedList from "@/components/article/NumberedList.astro";
import { donaid } from "@/data/donaid";
import { getNextShowcase, getShowcase } from "@/data/showcase";

const currentShowcase = getShowcase("donaid");
const nextShowcase = getNextShowcase("donaid");
---

<ArticleShell title="DonAid - Firas Razak">
  <ArticleHeader />

  <ArticleHero showcase={currentShowcase}>
    <Fragment slot="summary">
      <p>
        <strong>Public trust in charitable giving</strong> is often shaken by concerns
        over fraud, misuse of funds, and opaque money handling. These issues can <strong
          >turn an act of goodwill into a leap of faith</strong
        >
        for donors.
      </p>
      <p>
        By making <strong>donation traceable, like parcel tracking</strong>,
        donors and partners can see how money moves from collection to charity.
      </p>
    </Fragment>
  </ArticleHero>

  <ArticleSection
    id="background-title"
    title="Background"
    class="background"
    alignStart
  >
    <BackgroundMeta meta={donaid.backgroundMeta}>
      3 development attempts had failed, and other prospective agencies were
      unresponsive. Without a clear specification, previous teams were forced to
      guess, often mistaking the donation tracking system for a standard
      donation platform. The issue was in comprehension, not engineering.
    </BackgroundMeta>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection id="problems-title" title="Problems">
    <NumberedList items={donaid.problems} />
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection
    id="workshop-title"
    title="Product workshop"
    dense
    titleOffset
    alignStart
  >
    <p class="section-copy">
      To start, I ran daily sessions with the founder until we reached enough
      shared understanding of the product. I then simplified the original
      material into a 7-page product brief to be sent to development agencies
      for quotation. After the rewrite,
      <strong>agency response rate increased from 10% to 80%.</strong>
    </p>
    <div class="media-grid workshop-grid">
      {donaid.workshopFigures.map((figure) => <MediaFigure figure={figure} />)}
    </div>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection
    id="feasibility-title"
    title="Feasibility study"
    dense
    titleOffset
    alignStart
  >
    <p class="section-copy">
      I surveyed banking and messaging integrations to map what could be
      automated, what needed vendor buy-in, and what required a manual fallback.
      Where banks moved too slow, I proposed processing the banking side
      manually as an interim workaround.
    </p>
    <div class="media-grid two-col">
      {
        donaid.feasibilityFigures.map((figure) => (
          <MediaFigure figure={figure} />
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection
    id="process-title"
    title="Work scoping"
    dense
    titleOffset
    alignStart
  >
    <p class="section-copy">
      I split the brief into Demo, MVP, and Feature Complete phases. I also
      shifted the founder's mindset to agile workflow.
    </p>
    <div class="media-grid two-col">
      {donaid.processFigures.map((figure) => <MediaFigure figure={figure} />)}
    </div>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection
    id="interface-title"
    title="Interface design"
    class="interface-design"
  >
    <p class="section-copy start">
      Design was not in the agency's scope. I stepped in and delivered
      interfaces and flow diagrams in sync with dev milestones.
    </p>
    <MediaFigure
      figure={donaid.interfaceFigure}
      titleSuffix=":"
      class="interface-figure"
    />
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection
    id="checkins-title"
    title="Engineering check-ins"
    titleOffset
    alignStart
  >
    <p class="section-copy">
      I ran weekly check-ins, taking progress reports from the dev team while
      handing over design for the next task. I bridged the founder and dev
      across system design, business logic, architecture, and acceptance
      criteria.
    </p>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection id="features-title" title="Product core feature" dense>
    <p class="section-copy start">
      DonAid's main scope is to verify a donation after the transaction and
      track the money received from a campaign partner to the auditing trustee
      and finally released to the charity.
    </p>
    <MediaFigure
      figure={donaid.blueprintFigure}
      titleSuffix=":"
      class="blueprint"
    />
    <FeatureList features={donaid.features} />
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection id="outcome-title" title="Outcome" dense>
    <p class="section-copy start">
      The final delivery hit a foreseeable delay for the bank integration scope
      since the founder and the team had agreed to push ahead despite the flag
      to omit it.
    </p>
    <MediaFigure
      figure={donaid.outcomeFigure}
      titleSuffix=":"
      class="outcome-card"
    />
    <p class="pull-quote">
      After the demo deployment, the founder and I had conducted a market-fit
      demonstration. <strong>All 32 attendants</strong> from various
      <strong>charity organisations expressed interest</strong> in the product and
      demonstrated a <strong>thorough understanding</strong> how donation tracking
      works.
    </p>
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleSection id="insights-title" title="Insights" class="insights">
    <InsightList insights={donaid.insights} />
  </ArticleSection>

  <ArticleFooter next={nextShowcase} />
</ArticleShell>

<style is:global>
  .article .media-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .article .workshop-grid,
  .article .process-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .article .pull-quote {
    padding-block: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .article .insights {
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 64rem) {
    .article .media-grid {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .article .media-grid.two-col {
      grid-column: 2 / -1;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .article .pull-quote {
      grid-column: 1 / span 2;
      padding-block: 0;
      color: var(--text-normal);
      font-size: 1.875rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }

    .article .insights {
      padding-top: 6rem;
    }
  }
</style>
